      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Superstar LEAP TO FAME (7) makes his return to Brisbane after adding to his legendary status with some brilliant performances in the last few months, highlighted by a second Miracle Mile crown and another victory in The Race in NZ at his latest appearance in April. Kept up to the mark with an easy trial win and has won a phenomenal 18 of 20 attempts at this circuit and distance. Should be a class above these. WISPER A SECRET (3) hasn't raced since the Blacks a Fake last December where he was down the track but he owns a good fresh record and has been readied with two trial placings, the latest a second to LEAP TO FAME. Draws well and he is a Group 1 winner here so has trifecta claims as does ATTACHMENT (6) who draws wide but continued his good form when runner-up to a smart one in The Janitor last week. TIMS A TROOPER (5) is honest and could round out the top four.",
